features: Do you need to extend WiFi outside? Does your Wi-Fi limit you to streaming live videos, photos from your backyard pool? WAVLINK brings the latest excellent long range outdoor Wi-Fi extender with a lot of flexibility and advanced features, making it ideal for extending WiFi signal to long-range, large areas. Perfect for big area, house, farm, garden, garage, backyard, street, property, office and outdoors.

Dual Band Outdoor Router: Complies with IEEE 802 11 ac/a/b/g/n standards. With a brand-new chip MT7621A. Waterproof WiFi extender supports AP, Repeater, Router. Multiple modes meet most of your demands.

Outdoor waterproof design: IP65-rated weatherproof & heat-resistant case that ensure stable connection in harsh outdoor conditions. The key parts have been coated with waterproof glue to strictly avoid leakage phenomenon of the product.

Power Over Ethernet: Integrated Power over Ethernet (PoE) supported, allowing it to be installed in areas where power outlet is not available by combing your power. Dual Gigabit (1000Mbps) LAN/WAN Ethernet Ports---support 10/100/1000Mbps speeds.
4 x 7dBi Omnidirectional Antennas: Higher antenna gain extensively strengthens Wi-Fi signal. High Power Amplifiers and enhanced receiver design for more strong penetration & longer range coverage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I installed this on my gazebo outside my house, so that I could put a wireless camera on my front gate which is approximately 100 yards away from my house. I was amazed that I got a signal that far away. It's only two bars for the most part, but I still have the signal. Connecting it through my phone was easy and quick. Totally recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Talk about some power!
reviews.reviewText: I got this device to increase my WiFi coverage on our Horse Farm, as I wanted to install WiFi Cameras at the corners of our property. I was hoping to get around 1100' out of the Wavlink after installing it on my roof.As it turns out, I was able to leave the Wavlink in my attic and have it broadcast well beyond the corners of my property.The HD6 was easy to install and set up. I usually don't write reviews, but thought I needed to, as this product is doing such an outstanding job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars No customer support
reviews.reviewText: A person of average computer skills will have great difficulty hooking this up. There is no legitimate customer support. For 3 days I worked on this and tried for hours on end to make a connection with customer support. Automated voice saying you were second in que. You get this message twice then they disconnect. I have Starlink Internet and I could never get it to connect. I couldn't get updated firmware because I couldn't set it up. Advanced computer skills MIGHT get further with this but I personally think that the lack of customer support makes it uselessAfter a request from the company to try this product again, and with their guided help through Amazon messaging and personal help through one of THEIR support staff's FB connection, I was able to connect the repeater and it is working great. I have tested it through a power failure and it reconnected with no issues and the extended signal seems strong and consistent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works as advertised
reviews.reviewText: I was having a little difficulty setting it up (user error), but tech support was quick to answer my call and get me going. I placed the unit in my cooking shed in the back yard where I used to get no signal. Now we're watching streaming tv with no problems!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Works great sometimes.
reviews.reviewText: Jury still out, but very difficult to configure, wifi seems to intermittently go down, but comes back a while later. If i can figure out how to keep the wifi up all the time, I would give this 4-5 stars and say it's worth the investment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It works but not as I hoped.
reviews.reviewText: I have a 360 ft driveway with a solar Wi-Fi camera and Wi-Fi gate controller. I ran 300 feet of cat 5 from inside the house and was able to locate this extender within 150 ft of the end of my driveway due to the routing path of the cable. It works but both devices are giving me alerts that the Wi-Fi signal is weak. I was hoping for better as it advertises 3000 sq ft coverage. I suppose its within that but not optimal. I can't give 5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty Good Deal
reviews.reviewText: The power over Ethernet plug and cat6 box will need to go in a separate weatherproof junction box as pictured. I used a Cantex 6” but a 4” will work fine. The antennae need to be put in the proper holes, 5g and 2g are not interchangeable.I can get about 250’ outdoor range with this up on a 15ft. power pole. For my neighbors to get internet inside their homes we used an additional Netgear extender on their property. Now my neighbors are all on Starlink. So long Hughes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars WAVLINK Outdoor WiFi 6 Extender
reviews.reviewText: This wifi external works great. Get a good signal about 100 yards away. A+
O sinal é bem amplo, facil instalação!

Habe es nun einen Monat im Einsatz, bisher kann ich mich nur dran erfreuen.Vorher habe ich mit Fritz DLan gearbeitet, da dies mein Router ständig gestört hat und die Empfangsstärke auch eher miserabel waren habe ich mich für die WLAN Antenne/access point entschieden.Über Repeater funktion kann ich nichts sagen.Ich habe ein LAN Kabel vom Router über unseren Dachboden gelegt und dann nach Aussen gebohrt. Nach kurzer Einstellung war das Internet voll funktionsfähig und ohne Abbrüche da.Am Ende des Gartens (105m) sind noch 85-90% der Internetleistung über WLAN ohne Probleme.Unsere Überwachungskamera und PV Shelly EM laufen nun auch besser, da der Empfang stärker ist. Bin sehr zufrieden damit.
Très bon produit très facile. À paramétrer.

El WAVLINK WiFi6 es como el jet privado de la conectividad, ¡te lleva a donde necesitas ir con estilo! Desde que lo instalé, la velocidad se ha vuelto mi mejor amiga.Ventajas:Velocidad Asombrosa: Descargas e streaming más rápidos que una llamada de emergencia.Cobertura Total: Mi señal sigue fuerte incluso en la "tierra de nadie" de mi casa.Configuración Sencilla: La instalación es tan fácil que casi siento que merezco un título en tecnología.Desventajas:Precio un Poco Elevado: La elegancia tiene su precio, y este router no es la excepción.Algo Voluminoso: No es el router más compacto, así que asegúrate de tener suficiente espacio en tu estación de comandos.En resumen, el WAVLINK WiFi6 es un caballero con corbata que te ofrece velocidad y elegancia. ¿Vale la pena la inversión? ¡Absolutamente! Pero asegúrate de tener el espacio para este elegante miembro . 🌐💼

reviews.reviewText: Im a farm, farm shop, campsite.I had fibre installed to my farm shop, speeds up to 150mbps :)Problem was only in the shop.I plugged this in &..............Signal in Shop, farmhouse, campsite, workshop, everywhere.Negative: It prompts you to upgrade its firmware.
